reviewText:
Early Access Review

If you’re wondering what you’ll be doing when the world reaches its end, or well, when human society collapses, let’s just hope it’s not what Fallen: A2P Protocol wants you to do, kill everyone, even if they’re bad guys and all. Who am I kidding, the more the merrier!

This is the way the world ends. Not with a bang but a whimper.

T.S. Eliot

Without any further delay, I present to you my review of Fallen: A2P Protocol.

GameplayFrom the captivating design of the maps, to every small detail, Fallen: A2P Protocol has the looks of an amazing game.
Following a story mode, it’s up to the player to choose the right moves, as well as the right weapon for the job, which can be a katana, a stop sign, an SMG, or even a sniper rifle.
The game also allows the player to choose which mission should be next, using a map and a vehicle, a caravan, to be more accurate. Since resourcers are scarce, driving around indefinitely is not an option, as there’s a sort of fuel resource limit. It’s also on the caravan that the player gets to use the hard earned experience to improve the unit’s skills, and even to gear them up, among other options.
If you’re looking for a good turn-based game, with an apocalyptic setting to it, and a bright future ahead of it, look no further.

Pros Great graphics;
Fantastic environment, incredibly well designed, givin a post-apocalyptic feeling to the game;
The AI is really solid;
Sound effects are well suited to the genre;
Nice variety of weapons;
Diversified maps.
Considering it's an Early Access (EA) game, I've decided to add a Neutral" category

